00:28:40,170 --> 00:28:42,480
Tell me about it.

500
00:28:43,020 --> 00:28:45,170
That's ridiculous.

501
00:28:48,290 --> 00:28:52,960
The student is the one who is responsible for the outcome.

502
00:28:53,540 --> 00:28:56,360
The student is the one who holds a pen and takes the exam.

503
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:58,740
It has nothing to with parents.

504
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:04,630
It's my duty to teach students with all my might if they need my help.

505
00:29:06,170 --> 00:29:08,200
Harumi-sensei.

506
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:12,610
I had no idea you feel so passionate about the job.

507
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:17,510
Your personality has changed somehow, Harumi-sensei.

508
00:29:17,510 --> 00:29:18,930
Excuse me?

509
00:29:23,710 --> 00:29:27,640
What happened? What's wrong?

510
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:30,060
I... strained my back.

511
00:29:30,060 --> 00:29:33,100
- Are you okay?
- Stay back! It's contagious.

512
00:29:33,100 --> 00:29:35,250
Contagious? A strained back?

513
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:38,190
Please return to your seats. It's dangerous.

514
00:29:38,190 --> 00:29:39,700
I think I've heard that before...

515
00:29:39,700 --> 00:29:43,700
If I remember correctly, it is contagious...

516
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:47,610
<i>[Junko Harumi]</i>

517
00:30:04,550 --> 00:30:07,450
- I'll take care of this.
- Oh!

518
00:30:07,450 --> 00:30:11,600
Call her now. Why not settle your twenty-year long

519
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:14,120
unrequited love?

520
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:17,350
Don't make it sound like I'm some kind of weirdo.

521
00:30:17,350 --> 00:30:19,050
I'm just stating the fact.

522
00:30:19,050 --> 00:30:23,510
A person becomes a full-grown adult in twenty years! It's the life span

523
00:30:23,510 --> 00:30:25,830
- of a panda-
- Okay, I see your point.

524
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:28,760
If you do, take prompt action.

525
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:33,050
Your cousin might be at a matchmaking party right as we speak...

526
00:30:33,050 --> 00:30:37,070
Even if she's in her thirties who failed in a college exam, job hunting, or getting married...

527
00:30:37,070 --> 00:30:38,470
Hold on now.

528
00:30:38,470 --> 00:30:40,720
Those all true,

529
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:42,700
but don't speak badly of her.

530
00:30:42,700 --> 00:30:47,300
Sorry. You seemed so pathetic, incompetent, spineless-

531
00:30:47,300 --> 00:30:50,540
Hold on!

532
00:30:50,540 --> 00:30:53,440
I was about to call her now.

533
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:55,370
Then do it.

534
00:30:55,370 --> 00:30:58,270
Do it. Right now.

535
00:30:58,270 --> 00:31:00,670
Okay, I'm calling her.

536
00:31:11,660 --> 00:31:15,710
Hello, Junko. This is last minute, but...

537
00:31:15,710 --> 00:31:18,530
What? It's not a good time?

538
00:31:18,530 --> 00:31:20,140
I see.

539
00:31:20,140 --> 00:31:22,570
It's good that you're busy.

540
00:31:23,950 --> 00:31:26,000
Do you have a question?

541
00:31:28,780 --> 00:31:31,060
What does it mean when a high school boy

542
00:31:31,060 --> 00:31:34,480
rest his head on your lap and glares at you?

543
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:38,080
The young rival is aggressive!

544
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:42,510
Well... that means, Junko.

545
00:31:42,510 --> 00:31:45,390
You know...

546
00:31:45,390 --> 00:31:49,370
a pubescent boy does that to a random girl who means nothing to him.

547
00:31:49,370 --> 00:31:52,590
I also used to do that to girls who I wasn't interested in

548
00:31:52,590 --> 00:31:56,350
all the time. Not just on their laps,

549
00:31:56,350 --> 00:31:59,860
I rested my head on their elbows, ankles, and all sorts of places.

550
00:31:59,860 --> 00:32:02,160
Ouch. It hurts.
<i>[Sanno Seminar]</i>

551
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:04,620
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

552
00:32:04,620 --> 00:32:09,400
Next time, could you bring your middle school textbooks?

553
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,750
Sure.

554
00:32:11,490 --> 00:32:12,930
There you are.

555
00:32:12,930 --> 00:32:16,260
Thank you for the other day.  I'm Mika Eto.

556
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:19,310
- Are you...?
- What?

557
00:32:20,260 --> 00:32:22,700
I can't believe you forgot.

558
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:28,750
I'm Mika Eto, student at 11th grade of Asakura Girls' High. I'll be joining this cram school!

559
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:32,260
Really? Please, come this way.

560
00:32:32,260 --> 00:32:34,140
Hey.

561
00:32:34,140 --> 00:32:35,770
How do you find out about this place?

562
00:32:35,770 --> 00:32:37,730
It wasn't easy to find you.

563
00:32:37,730 --> 00:32:41,250
The girl who went to middle school with you didn't know...

564
00:32:41,250 --> 00:32:43,610
I searched you on Twitter, Instagram, Facebook...

565
00:32:43,610 --> 00:32:47,030
But I couldn't find you anywhere on social media.

566
00:32:47,030 --> 00:32:48,940
Then finally...

567
00:32:48,940 --> 00:32:52,060
I found the hamburg steak guy.

568
00:32:52,060 --> 00:32:55,670
<i>Hamburg steak!</i>

569
00:32:55,670 --> 00:32:57,660
He made me buy him a hamburg steak...

570
00:32:57,660 --> 00:33:00,240
- So he is the traitor.
- Oh!

571
00:33:01,840 --> 00:33:05,220
You're the scary blame-shifter!

572
00:33:06,310 --> 00:33:09,240
This is all your fault, Kyo.

573
00:33:11,460 --> 00:33:14,540
Youngsters sure have their ways.

574
00:33:14,540 --> 00:33:17,230
You can pass your exam and fall in love!

575
00:33:17,230 --> 00:33:18,930
You just want to get a pay raise, don't you?

576
00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:23,910
I'm just trying to avoid a pay cut. Don't underestimate "the exploitative cram school".

577
00:33:23,910 --> 00:33:27,350
Ms. Eto, you can complete your registration here.

578
00:33:27,350 --> 00:33:29,110
This way, please.

579
00:33:29,110 --> 00:33:31,840
She's a new student. Please help her with her application.

580
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:36,980
Sorry, Kyohei.

581
00:33:36,980 --> 00:33:40,000
But that hamburg steak was delicious.

582
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:40,990
It was so juicy.

583
00:33:40,990 --> 00:33:43,380
- You are annoying.
- It was juicy.

584
00:33:43,380 --> 00:33:45,400
Whoa!

585
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:48,330
What a cool car.

586
00:33:48,330 --> 00:33:52,400
There you are, Kyo. Is it true what she says?

587
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:54,000
Why can't we study together?

588
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:57,360
I told you, our cram school tutors students individually!

589
00:33:57,360 --> 00:33:58,910
Jun.

590
00:33:59,470 --> 00:34:02,680
Masashi, what brings you here?

591
00:34:03,620 --> 00:34:08,660
<i>Masashi, I'm really sorry. I have to cancel today's dinner.</i>

592
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:12,670
Matsuoka told me you strained your back again.

593
00:34:12,670 --> 00:34:15,510
I was in the area, so I figured I'd take you home.

594
00:34:15,510 --> 00:34:18,270
What? Zunko-sensei, did you have a boyfriend?

595
00:34:18,270 --> 00:34:20,490
No, he's my cousin.

596
00:34:20,490 --> 00:34:24,140
Oh, cousin?

597
00:34:24,140 --> 00:34:27,640
Are you the one who's aiming to get into the University of Tokyo?

598
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:30,210
- What? The University of Tokyo?
- That's right.

599
00:34:30,210 --> 00:34:31,690
This is Kyohei Yuri.

600
00:34:31,690 --> 00:34:36,080
He's aiming for the science courses, so I might ask for your help in the future!

601
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:40,370
If a guy like you with pink hair gets in,

602
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:42,500
that university may become a little interesting.

603
00:34:42,500 --> 00:34:44,830
Are you a graduate of the University of Tokyo?

604
00:34:45,340 --> 00:34:47,780
I'll help you out anytime since you're Jun's student.

605
00:34:47,780 --> 00:34:49,360
No, thanks.

606
00:34:50,700 --> 00:34:52,490
I'll manage on my own.

607
00:34:57,330 --> 00:35:00,870
Good. That's the spirit!

608
00:35:00,870 --> 00:35:03,220
Oh, no.  I have to get going.

609
00:35:03,220 --> 00:35:04,700
Are you going somewhere?

610
00:35:04,700 --> 00:35:08,280
A seminar for cram school teachers. I have to study, too.

611
00:35:08,280 --> 00:35:09,400
Should I drive you there?

612
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:11,740
Really? That'd be great.

613
00:35:11,740 --> 00:35:13,380
Take care, guys.

614
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:15,990
- Bye bye.
- Bye.

615
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:20,980
Bye bye.

616
00:35:20,980 --> 00:35:26,080
I've never thought Junko-sensei has such an elite cousin.

617
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:30,990
He probably knows a lot of elites he can introduce her to.

618
00:35:31,750 --> 00:35:33,380
Kyo.

619
00:35:36,950 --> 00:35:39,460
You like that teacher, don't you?

620
00:35:41,670 --> 00:35:43,860
I can understand how you feel a little.

621
00:35:43,860 --> 00:35:48,780
My mom raised me by herself, so I'm attracted to older

622
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:51,460
and mature guys.

623
00:35:54,050 --> 00:35:55,950
It's not what you think.

624
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:58,960
Don't tell her anything stupid.

625
00:36:01,030 --> 00:36:02,820
Let's head home.

626
00:36:02,820 --> 00:36:05,280
- Huh? Okay. Are we going home?
- Yeah.

627
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:06,760
<i>Why don't we eat something first?</i>

628
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:09,810
A student of Minami High is aiming for the University of Tokyo...

629
00:36:10,980 --> 00:36:14,470
But he's improved so much in a short period of time.

630
00:36:14,470 --> 00:36:17,370
I hope a miracle occurs.

631
00:36:18,370 --> 00:36:19,800
You know...

632
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:25,170
when I look at that boy, I've started to realize something.

633
00:36:25,170 --> 00:36:27,290
Like what?

634
00:36:27,290 --> 00:36:30,000
I realized that studying is fun.

635
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:35,690
Miracles do happen.

636
00:36:36,710 --> 00:36:39,060
There was a guy in a research room at college.

637
00:36:39,060 --> 00:36:42,590
He didn't study until he got into high school.

638
00:36:42,590 --> 00:36:46,230
But he had an extraordinary ability to focus

639
00:36:46,230 --> 00:36:51,490
on games and everything, not only for studying.

640
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:55,520
He was also self-motivated.

641
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:58,790
Then, he will be fine.

642
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:02,840
<i>He has great concentration and self-motivation.</i>

643
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:07,330
<i>At least more than I did in the past.</i>

644
00:37:09,140 --> 00:37:13,860
I want him to become the person he wants to be.

645
00:37:17,890 --> 00:37:20,620
<i>[Minami High School]</i>

646
00:37:20,620 --> 00:37:26,450
I'm sorry. I ended up giving a lecture in your class, Yamashita.

647
00:37:26,450 --> 00:37:30,480
I'm actually looking forward to your lecture tomorrow.

648
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:45,470
<i>Even teachers should apologize when they made mistakes.</i>

649
00:37:48,870 --> 00:37:50,820
- Ito.
- What?

650
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:58,240
I'm sorry about the other day.

651
00:37:58,240 --> 00:38:00,630
I was wrong to accuse you.

652
00:38:00,630 --> 00:38:03,170
Why, out of the blue?

653
00:38:03,950 --> 00:38:08,710
I thought I should hear you out.

654
00:38:08,710 --> 00:38:11,010
Hey. Did you really not do it?

655
00:38:11,010 --> 00:38:13,090
You are annoying.

656
00:38:13,090 --> 00:38:15,110
Watch out!

657
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:33,090
Yuri-yuri?

658
00:38:39,460 --> 00:38:41,400
<i>[Yuri]</i>

659
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:49,560
We sincerely apologize for what happened today.

660
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:54,650
Please, raise your head. My son told me it wasn't your fault.

661
00:38:55,490 --> 00:38:57,820
Please, sit down.

662
00:39:03,550 --> 00:39:08,910
But, Ms. Harumi. I don't want you to teach my son anymore.

663
00:39:08,910 --> 00:39:10,520
Hey, Dad!

664
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:12,460
Stay out of this.

665
00:39:12,460 --> 00:39:14,090
Well...

666
00:39:14,090 --> 00:39:16,380
I'm sorry.

667
00:39:16,380 --> 00:39:19,560
What happened was all due to my negligence.

668
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:20,610
She just happened to be there.

669
00:39:20,610 --> 00:39:22,770
It has nothing to do with his injury.

670
00:39:22,770 --> 00:39:25,370
It's about her ability.

671
00:39:25,370 --> 00:39:28,910
I'm sorry, but I looked into your educational background,

672
00:39:28,910 --> 00:39:33,290
work history, and achievements.

673
00:39:33,290 --> 00:39:38,540
I don't believe you are capable of helping my son get into even a private college, let alone the University of Tokyo.

674
00:39:38,540 --> 00:39:42,080
You are underqualified. Do you have any objections?

675
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:48,470
I hear cram school teachers are evaluated based on their popularity as well.

676
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:51,060
So I understand your situation.

677
00:39:51,060 --> 00:39:55,440
However, it bothers me when you use my son as a steeping stone.

678
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:57,080
I'll make him go to a different cram school.

679
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:59,230
Cut the crap.

680
00:40:00,190 --> 00:40:02,770
I understand.

681
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:10,500
But, I have one favor to ask of you.

682
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:16,120
Please never discourage him now.

683
00:40:17,630 --> 00:40:22,080
No matter how desperate the parents are or how much money they spend,

684
00:40:22,080 --> 00:40:26,660
you can't buy his self-motivation and concentration with money.

685
00:40:28,410 --> 00:40:30,590
As his teacher,

686
00:40:30,590 --> 00:40:33,030
this is my last wish.

687
00:40:41,670 --> 00:40:44,150
<i>[Minami High School]</i>

688
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:46,240
<i>[Grade-11th, Class-A]</i>

689
00:40:52,830 --> 00:40:54,420
Hey!

690
00:40:54,420 --> 00:40:56,980
Oh, yes.

691
00:41:04,460 --> 00:41:06,040
Is everyone here?

692
00:41:06,040 --> 00:41:07,990
We're all here.

693
00:41:12,810 --> 00:41:16,720
Nice to meet you, students of Minami High School.

694
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:19,100
I came from Sanno Seminar.

695
00:41:19,100 --> 00:41:21,250
My name is Harumi.

696
00:41:22,030 --> 00:41:24,530
Today, I'm going to...

697
00:41:28,940 --> 00:41:31,700
No one is listening.

698
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:33,990
Hey, you guys. Face forward.

699
00:41:33,990 --> 00:41:37,550
Teacher, what's your bra size?

700
00:41:37,550 --> 00:41:40,190
Idiot. She won't tell us!

701
00:41:40,190 --> 00:41:44,100
I mean, how will studying help us?

702
00:41:44,100 --> 00:41:46,160
It's useless.

703
00:42:01,210 --> 00:42:03,620
I totally agree.

704
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:11,540
I don't mean to brag, but I've studied so hard since I was young.

705
00:42:11,540 --> 00:42:17,220
And it didn't help me a bit when I searched for a job or a husband.

706
00:42:18,460 --> 00:42:23,020
I studied without thinking, just because I was told to.

707
00:42:26,090 --> 00:42:29,400
As a result, I'm here right now,

708
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:32,480
giving you a lecture to promote my school.

709
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:35,800
I'm a screw-up teacher on the verge of getting fired.

710
00:42:37,540 --> 00:42:40,260
You are no good, then!

711
00:42:42,230 --> 00:42:47,000
So if you think studying is meaningless,

712
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:49,670
then don't study.

713
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:54,940
But you know...

714
00:42:54,940 --> 00:42:58,320
even if you don't care about yourself,

715
00:42:59,030 --> 00:43:01,790
what about when you have someone you care about?

716
00:43:01,790 --> 00:43:05,150
Not being able to protect your beloved person will be

717
00:43:05,150 --> 00:43:08,670
more miserable than not being able to protect yourself.

718
00:43:09,340 --> 00:43:13,890
When you marry someone and get a loan for a house,

719
00:43:13,890 --> 00:43:18,840
and pensions, medical and life insurance in case of occurrences.

720
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:24,070
It's your loss if you don't study at least to understand the complicated contracts.

721
00:43:24,070 --> 00:43:26,370
You could get scammed in the worst case.

722
00:43:27,460 --> 00:43:30,570
You think it's still a long way ahead.

723
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:35,110
But you'll be surprised when you passed thirty,

724
00:43:35,110 --> 00:43:38,230
your back and knees will suddenly get weakened.

725
00:43:38,230 --> 00:43:39,880
Especially your lower back.

726
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:43,440
- I don't want to carry you again.
- It looked painful.

727
00:43:43,440 --> 00:43:45,560
And...

728
00:43:45,560 --> 00:43:49,880
when you have a child who looks just like you in the future,

729
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:53,790
you will want to support their dream.

730
00:43:53,790 --> 00:43:59,660
What if you lack knowledge, wisdom, or ability in order to do so?

731
00:44:02,850 --> 00:44:08,590
Imagine what kind of person you want to be.

732
00:44:08,590 --> 00:44:12,170
And think what kind of studies do you need to become that person.

733
00:44:14,120 --> 00:44:19,180
The knowledge and effort you gain from studying

734
00:44:19,180 --> 00:44:22,940
will surely help you, even when

735
00:44:22,940 --> 00:44:25,970
you screw up in your life like I have.

736
00:44:32,520 --> 00:44:35,500
So I wish you the best of luck.

737
00:44:35,500 --> 00:44:37,330
For your own sake,

738
00:44:37,330 --> 00:44:40,840
and the sake of your precious people in your future.

739
00:44:46,430 --> 00:44:48,350
Teacher,

740
00:44:49,590 --> 00:44:55,630
I want you to teach me first how to find your beloved person.

741
00:44:58,310 --> 00:45:01,360
Sorry, I'd like to know that myself, too.

742
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:03,820
What? You don't know?

743
00:45:03,820 --> 00:45:06,170
Go to matchmaking parties.

744
00:45:06,170 --> 00:45:08,870
- By hitting on girls.
- There is no way you could.

745
00:45:08,870 --> 00:45:12,840
- I'd like to hit on girls.
- I like doing both.

746
00:45:14,050 --> 00:45:18,870
It was my first time seeing my students listen quietly to a lecture.

747
00:45:18,870 --> 00:45:21,340
It wasn't what I originally planned, though.

748
00:45:21,340 --> 00:45:23,000
You haven't changed.

749
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:27,100
You are still you, Harumi.

750
00:45:28,070 --> 00:45:29,960
Yamashita...

751
00:45:30,500 --> 00:45:34,230
This is my phone number.

752
00:45:34,230 --> 00:45:38,640
If you hurt your back again, call me. I know a good chiropractor.

753
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:40,000
Thanks. I appreciate it.

754
00:45:41,490 --> 00:45:44,510
- Then, I'll give you my number, too.
- Yeah.

755
00:45:44,510 --> 00:45:46,990
It's 090...

756
